cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper discusses the issues and assumptions of GANs, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees of GANs, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes an alternative method, which could also fall under the sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
